sub_title: Researcher and Consultant | Human Rights | Conflict & Peacebuilding | Political ecology & food systems
summary:
Sociologist and MA in Geography from the National University of Colombia. Freelance Illustrator and drawer. Currently MA student of Latin American studies at the University of Amsterdam.

Professional experience in research, fieldwork, and communitarian processes related to Colombia's environmental, conflict, and peace processes. I have worked in transitional justice processes in Colombia as a senior analyst at the Commission of Truth in the Colombian Magdalena River region. Also, I support the communitarian approach and institutional policies in the Rural Reform associated with the Peace agreement implementation. 

I worked with local peace-building processes with social organizations, non-governmental organizations and the institutional sector. My skills are in Data processing and managing, interviews, writing texts, brief documents and information. Also, I have skills in working with communities in complex contexts, fieldwork and group methodologies.

Language: English IELTS 7.5 Overall (C1)
